  <thing id="iBladeRWar" name="Blade of Righteous War" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 12,315 gp (13th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: &#151;(held)\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 7th\n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 18); evocation\n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151; or free; see text\n{b}Weight{/b}: 4 lb.\n\n{i}A blood groove runs down the center of this weapon&apos;s blade. Set into the pommel is a blood-red ruby, and within its crimson depths floats a deity&apos;s holy symbol.{/i}\n\nThis +1 {i}longsword{/i} is favored by paladins and certain clerics. Any time you roll a critical threat with the {i}blade of righteous war{/i}, you can sacrifice a turn/rebuke undead attempt as a free action to gain a +4 bonus on the roll made to confirm the critical threat. You must make this decision before making the confirmation roll.\n\nThe {i}blade of righteous war{/i} is part of a set known collectively as the {i}regalia of righteous war{/i}, which also includes the {i}helm of righteous war{/i} (page 139) and the {i}bastion of righteous war{/i} (see above). When you use all three together, you gain an additional benefit as noted in the description of the {i}bastion of righteous war{/i}. \n\nThe holy symbol pictured in the weapon&apos;s pommel always matches the deity worshiped by the holder (if any). \n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 6,000 gp (plus 315 gp for masterwork longsword), 480 XP, 12 days. \n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}divine power{/i}, turn or rebuke undead.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="MagicWep">
