  <thing id="ioBraDivLu" name="Bracers of Divine Luck" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 8,000 gp (11th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Arms\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 9th\n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 19); abjuration \n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151; \n{b}Weight{/b}: 2 lb.\n\n{i}These leather bracers are a deep burgundy color. Close examination reveals that the left bracer is stitched in patterns of seven, while the right is stitched in patterns of eleven.{/i}\n\nWhen you cast a divine spell while wearing these bracers, you gain a +1 luck bonus on attack rolls, saving throws, or AC (chosen at the time you cast the spell). This bonus lasts until the start of your next turn.\n\nIf you worship Olidammara (or any other deity that offers access to the Luck domain), the bonus instead applies to your attack rolls, saving throws, and Armor Class simultaneously.\n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 4,000 gp, 320 XP, 8 days.\n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, worshiper of Olidammara.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="2"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="8000"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpWrist"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xBraDivLuc"></bootstrap>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioCloDrBla" name="Cloak of the Dragon (Black)" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 6,000 gp (10th) \n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Shoulders \n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 10th \n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 20); transmutation \n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151; and standard \n{b}Weight{/b}: 1 lb.\n\n{i}This cloak consists of layers of tiny scales affixed to a thin leather backing.{/i}\n\nTen varieties of this item exist, each corresponding in hue to one of the five chromatic or the five metallic dragons. While you wear the cloak, you gain a +1 enhancement bonus to your natural armor bonus.\n\nIf you worship Bahamut or Tiamat (or any other draconic deity), you may activate the {i}cloak of the dragon{/i} once per day to grow a pair of draconic wings that grants you a fly speed (equal to your land speed) for 10 minutes. While this effect is active, you may use a breath weapon (as if you were a half-dragon matching the hue of your cloak; see MM 146) once. \n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 3,000 gp, 240 XP, 6 days. \n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}polymorph{/i}, worshiper of a draconic deity.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="6000"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpBack"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xCloDraBla"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000" index="2"><![CDATA[
     ~ Set the name, summary, and custdesc of our breath weapon based on the color of the cloak, this will need to be modified for all versions.
      var DC as number
      DC = 10 + herofield[tHitDice].value/2 + hero.child[aCON].field[aModBonus].value 
      DC = round(DC, 0, -1)

hero.childfound[xHlDBreath].field[livename].text = "Breath Weapon, 6d8 acid, 60 ft line (DC " & DC & ")"
hero.childfound[xHlDBreath].field[xSumm].text = "While Cloak of the Dragon's wings are active, you may breath once."
hero.childfound[xHlDBreath].field[CustDesc].text = "You have the ability to use a breath weapon once while the cloak of the dragon is activated as a Half Dragon of the same color as your cloak."]]></eval>
    <eval phase="UserPreLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      if (field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
        #enhancementbonus[hero.child[mNatural], 1]
        endif

     perform hero.childfound[xHlDBreath].delete[Helper.ShowSpec]
     perform hero.childfound[xHlDBreath].delete[Helper.ShowCharge]
     perform hero.childfound[xHlDBreath].delete[SpecSource.HalfDragon]
     perform hero.childfound[xHlDBreath].assign[SpecSource.CloDragon]]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioCloVaga" name="Cloak of the Vagabond" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 9,000 gp (12th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Shoulders\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 11th\n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 20); abjuration\n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151;\n{b}Weight{/b}: 1/2 lb.\n\n{i}This torn and tattered cloak is spattered with mud and looks to have been poorly made. Its original fabric was a particularly nauseating shade of yellow.{/i}\n\nWhile wearing the {i}cloak of the vagabond{/i}, you gain resistance 5 to cold and fire.\n\nThis cloak is part of a set known collectively as the {i}garb of the vagabond{/i}, which also includes the {i}robe of the vagabond{/i}, the {i}sandals of the vagabond{/i}, and the {i}staff of the vagabond{/i}. When you wear a {i}cloak of the vagabond{/i} while using any two of the other items, it also grants you resistance 5 to electricity. When you use all four set items together, the {i}staff of the vagabond{/i} gains an extra benefit (see page 137).\n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 4,500 gp, 360 XP, 9 days.\n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}resist energy{/i}.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value=".5"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="9000"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpBack"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRsElec"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRsFire"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xCloVaga"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRsCold"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="First"><![CDATA[  if (field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
     #applyresist[xDamRsCold, 5]
     #applyresist[xDamRsFire, 5]

~ Figure out, if cloak is equipped, how many others are equipped?
      var cloakbonus as number
      cloakbonus = 0

      if (hero.childfound[iStaffVaga].field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
        cloakbonus += 1
      endif
      if (hero.childfound[ioRobeVaga].field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
        cloakbonus += 1
      endif
      if (hero.childfound[ioSandVaga].field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
        cloakbonus += 1
      endif

~ If at least 2 others are, apply more energy resistance.
    if (cloakbonus >= 2) then 
     #applyresist[xDamRsElec, 5]
    endif
  endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioCreValor" name="Crest of Valor" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 2,000 gp (6th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Head\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 7th\n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 18); enchantment\n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151;\n{b}Weight{/b}: &#151;\n\n{i}Designed to fit atop any helm, this crest is actually a small golden statuette of a griffon. Behind it trails a long, blood-red plume that could well be visible even across afield of battle.{/i}\n\nWhile wearing a {i}crest of valor{/i}, you gain a +2 morale bonus on melee weapon damage rolls while your current hit point total is equal to or less than one-half of your full normal hit points.\n\nThe {i}crest of valor{/i} is part of a set known collectively as the {i}raiment of valor{/i}, which also includes the {i}periapt of valor{/i} (page 140) and the {i}tabard of valor{/i} (page 142). When wearing all three of these items, all allies within 10 feet of you (including yourself) gain a +4 morale bonus on saves against fear effects.\n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 1,000 gp, 80 XP, 2 days.\n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}prayer{/i}, {i}remove fear{/i}.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
    <comment>Need to make specials (Done)

Test the Raimant special.... (Done)

Page 139 &#150; Crest of Valor
[Addition]
The bonus type in the last sentence
of the item&#146;s descriptive text
should be morale.</comment>
