  <thing id="ioPerValor" name="Periapt of Valor" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 4,000 gp (8th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Throat\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 7th\n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 18); enchantment\n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151;\n{b}Weight{/b}: &#151;\n\n{i}Hanging on a thin mithral chain is a tiny charm, on which i carved an odd combination of the holy symbols of Heironeous and Kord.{/i}\n\nWhile wearing a {i}periapt of valor{/i}, you gain a +2 morale bonus on AC and saving throws while your current hit point total is equal to or less than one-half of your full normal hit points.\n\nThe {i}periapt of valor{/i} is part of a set known collectively as the {i}raiment of valor{/i}. When you wear it along with a {i}crest of valor{/i} (page 139) and a {i}tabard of valor{/i} (page 142), you gain additional abilities as given in the description of the {i}crest of valor{/i}.\n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 2,000 gp, 160 XP, 4 days.\n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}good hope{/i} or {i}prayer{/i}, {i}lesser restoration{/i}.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
