  <thing id="irBeastRin" name="Ring of the Beast" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 8,000 gp (11th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Rings\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 10th\n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 20); conjuration\n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151;\n{b}Weight{/b}: &#151;\n\n{i}This tiny ring is carved of smooth wood, and engravings of ivy run along its length.{/i}\n\nWhenever you cast a {i}summon nature&apos;s ally{/i} spell (whether normally or spontaneously), you can treat it as though it were one level higher than it is. For instance, if you cast {i}summon nature&apos;s ally III{/i} (or sacrifice a 3rd-level druid spell to spontaneously cast it), you can treat it as if you had cast {i}summon nature&apos;s ally IV{/i} instead. However, you cannot use a {i}ring of the beast{/i} to cast a {i}summon nature&apos;s ally{/i} spell of a level higher than you can normally cast (in the class that allows you to cast the {i}summon nature&apos;s ally{/i} spell). This ring continues to function even while you are using wild shape.\n\nThe {i}ring of the beast{/i} is part of a set collectively known as the {i}trappings of the beast{/i}. When you wear it along with {i}armor of the beast{/i} (page 135) and a {i}mantle of the beast{/i} (see above), you gain additional abilities, as noted in the {i}armor of the beast{/i} description.\n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 4,000 gp, 320 XP, 8 days.\n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Forge Ring, Heighten Spell, {i}summon nature&apos;s ally I{/i}, wild shape.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Ring">
