  <thing id="ioSandVaga" name="Sandals of the Vagabond" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 4,000 gp (8th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Feet\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 11th\n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 20); conjuration\n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151;\n{b}Weight{/b}: 1/2 lb.\n\n{i}The soles of these of dust-covered sandals are worn nearly paper-thin in spots, and the cracking leather straps seem likely to crumble to dust at any moment.{/i}\n\nWhile wearing {i}sandals of the vagabond{/i}, you gain a +2 luck bonus on initiative checks and immunity to exhaustion. You can still become fatigued normally, but any spell or effect that would cause you to become exhausted instead makes you merely fatigued. If you&apos;re already fatigued, any effect that would cause you to become exhausted merely extends your fatigue for the number of rounds the exhaustion would have applied.\n\nThese sandals are part of a set known collectively as the {i}garb of the vagabond{/i}, which also includes the {i}cloak of the vagabond{/i}, the {i}robe of the vagabond{/i}, and the {i}staff of the vagabond{/i}. Using three or more of these items together grants extra benefits, as described in the entries for {i}cloak of the vagabond{/i} and {i}staff of the vagabond{/i}.\n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 2,000 gp, 160 XP, 4 days.\n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}restoration{/i}.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
