  <thing id="ioTabValor" name="Tabard of Valor" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 16,000 gp (14th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Torso\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 7th\n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 18); enchantment\n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151;\n{b}Weight{/b}: 3 lb.\n\n{i}Emblazoned in blood-red hues across the chest of this gleaming white tabard is the lightning bolt symbol of Heironeous.{/i}\n\nWhenever your current hit point total is equal to or less than one-half of your full normal hit points, you gain the mettle ability: If you are affected by a spell that would normally have a reduced effect on a successful Fortitude or Will saving throw, it instead has no effect at all upon you if you save successfully. If you already have mettle from a class feature or some other source, you instead gain improved mettle, which halves the harmful effects of a spell on a failed Fortitude or Will save while still protecting you entirely on a successful save.\n\nThe {i}tabard of valor{/i} is part of a set known collectively as the {i}raiment of valor{/i}, which also includes the {i}crest of valor{/i} (page 139) and the {i}periapt of valor{/i} (page 140). When you use a tabard with both of the other items, you gain additional abilities, as noted in the description of the {i}crest of valor{/i}.\n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 8,000 gp, 640 XP, 16 days. \n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}good hope{/i} or {i}prayer{/i}.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
