  <thing id="xLiveBulwa" name="Bulwark of the Living" description="A good-aligned character who bears this +1 {i}blinding heavy wooden shield{/i} can expend a 4th-level or higher divine spell as a standard action to cast {i}death ward{/i} (PH 217) on himself." compset="Special" summary="Standard, burn 4th or higher level divine spell to cast {i}death ward{/i} on self."></thing>
  <thing id="iBowElven" name="Bow of Elvenkind" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 14,700 gp (14th) \n{b}Body Slot{/b}: &#151;(held) \n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 12th \n{b}Aura{/b}: Strong (DC 21); divination \n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151; \n{b}Weight{/b}: 3 lb. \n\n{i}Gleaming white wood and horn have been lovingly shaped into a massive, recurved longbow. The string shimmers like silver, and the bow hums when drawn, as if the wood had been tuned for musical purposes.{/i}\n\nThis +1 {i}composite longbow{/i} (+0 Str bonus) automatically adjusts its pull to match the Strength of any elf who wields it.\n\nIn the hands of a cleric of Corellon Larethian, a bow of elvenkind gains the seeking weapon property (DMG 225), and any critical hit with an arrow fired from the bow renders the target shaken for 5 rounds (a mind-affecting fear effect; Will DC 14 negates).\n\nFurthermore, any elf or cleric of Corellon Larethian who uses the bow with arrows from the quiver of elvenkind (page 144) gains the benefit of the Far Shot feat.\n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 7,000 gp (plus 700 gp for masterwork composite longbow), 560 XP, 14 days.\n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, doom, {i}true seeing{/i}, {i}doom{/i}, elf.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="MagicWep">
