  <thing id="xSandVaga" name="Sandals of the Vagabond" description="While wearing {i}sandals of the vagabond{/i}, you gain a +2 luck bonus on initiative checks and immunity to exhaustion. You can still become fatigued normally, but any spell or effect that would cause you to become exhausted instead makes you merely fatigued. If you&apos;re already fatigued, any effect that would cause you to become exhausted merely extends your fatigue for the number of rounds the exhaustion would have applied.\n\nThese sandals are part of a set known collectively as the {i}garb of the vagabond{/i}, which also includes the {i}cloak of the vagabond{/i}, the {i}robe of the vagabond{/i}, and the {i}staff of the vagabond{/i}." compset="Special" summary="Effects causing exhaustion reduced to fatigue, +2 luck bonus to Initiative.">
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpSourceEq"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xStaffVaga" name="Staff of the Vagabond" description="This masterwork/masterwork quarterstaff becomes a +1/+1 {i}quarterstaff{/i} as long as you are carrying no other weapons. (Natural weapons or unarmed attacks don&apos;t count, but weapons you carry in a {i}bag of holding{/i} or other container do.)\n\nThe {i}staff of the vagabond{/i} is part of a set known collectively as the {i}garb of the vagabond{/i}, which also includes the {i}cloak of the vagabond{/i}, the {i}robe of the vagabond{/i}, and the {i}sandals of the vagabond{/i}. When you wield the {i}staff of the vagabond{/i} while wearing any two of the other items, each end gains the merciful property (DMG 225). When you wield it while wearing all three of the other items, each end also gains the ki focus property (DMG 225)" compset="Special" summary="+1/+1 staff when only weapon carried, merciful w/3 set items, ki focus w/4.">
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpSourceEq"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xCloVaga" name="Cloak of the Vagabond" description="While wearing the {i}cloak of the vagabond{/i}, you gain resistance 5 to cold and fire.\n\nThis cloak is part of a set known collectively as the {i}garb of the vagabond{/i}, which also includes the {i}robe of the vagabond{/i}, the {i}sandals of the vagabond{/i}, and the {i}staff of the vagabond{/i}. When you wear a {i}cloak of the vagabond{/i} while using any two of the other items, it also grants you resistance 5 to electricity." compset="Special" summary="Gain resist cold and fire 5, with 3 set items add resist electricity 5.">
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpSourceEq"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xBootWandr" name="Boots of the Wanderer" description="While wearing {i}boots of the wanderer{/i}, you automatically succeed on any Constitution checks required for running or making a forced march.\n\nIf you are a worshiper of Fharlanghn (or any deity that offers access to the Travel domain), you also gain a +5-foot enhancement bonus to your land speed while wearing the boots." compset="Special" summary="Auto-succeed run/forced march Con chk, +5 to speed if worship Travel god.">
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpSourceEq"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xBraDivLuc" name="Bracers of Divine Luck" description="When you cast a divine spell while wearing these bracers, you gain a +1 luck bonus on attack rolls, saving throws, or AC (chosen at the time you cast the spell). This bonus lasts until the start of your next turn.\n\nIf you worship Olidammara (or any other deity that offers access to the Luck domain), the bonus instead applies to your attack rolls, saving throws, and Armor Class simultaneously." compset="Special" summary="When cast divine spell +1 to att, saves or AC for 1 rd, +1 to all if worship Luck god.">
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpSourceEq"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xCloDraBla" name="Cloak of the Dragon" description="Ten varieties of this item exist, each corresponding in hue to one of the five chromatic or the five metallic dragons. While you wear the cloak, you gain a +1 enhancement bonus to your natural armor bonus.\n\nIf you worship Bahamut or Tiamat (or any other draconic deity), you may activate the {i}cloak of the dragon{/i} once per day to grow a pair of draconic wings that grants you a fly speed (equal to your land speed) for 10 minutes. While this effect is active, you may use a breath weapon (as if you were a half-dragon matching the hue of your cloak; see MM 146) once." compset="Special" summary="1/day grow wings and fly for 10 min if worship draconic god.">
