  <thing id="ioAspPeSer" name="Aspergillum of Perpetual Serenity" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 1,500 gp (5th)\n{b}Body Slot{/b}: &#151; (held)\n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 3rd\n{b}Aura{/b}: Faint (DC 16); transmutation \n{b}Activation{/b}: Standard (manipulation) \n{b}Weight{/b}: 1 lb.\n\n{i}This small wooden shaft has a hollow ball at one end. Tiny holes in the ball allow axiomatic water to emerge from the font within.{/i}\n\nYou can use this vessel to dispense small amounts of axiomatic water. The reservoir holds a pint of axiomatic water, even though it does not appear large enough to contain such a quantity. Every dawn, an {i}aspergillum of perpetual serenity{/i} refills itself, ensuring you a nearly endless supply of axiomatic water. Axiomatic water dispensed from this item loses its blessing after 24 hours. \n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 750 gp, 60 XP, 2 days. \n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}axiomatic water{/i}.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
