  <thing id="xRingBeast" name="Ring of the Beast" description="Whenever you cast a {i}summon nature&apos;s ally{/i} spell (whether normally or spontaneously), you can treat it as though it were one level higher than it is. For instance, if you cast {i}summon nature&apos;s ally III{/i} (or sacrifice a 3rd-level druid spell to spontaneously cast it), you can treat it as if you had cast {i}summon nature&apos;s ally IV{/i} instead. However, you cannot use a {i}ring of the beast{/i} to cast a {i}summon nature&apos;s ally{/i} spell of a level higher than you can normally cast (in the class that allows you to cast the {i}summon nature&apos;s ally{/i} spell). This ring continues to function even while you are using wild shape.\n\nThe {i}ring of the beast{/i} is part of a set collectively known as the {i}trappings of the beast{/i}. When you wear it along with {i}armor of the beast{/i} (page 135) and a {i}mantle of the beast{/i} (see above), you gain additional abilities, as noted in the {i}armor of the beast{/i} description." compset="Special" summary="{i}Summon nature&apos;s ally{/i} cast at +1 spell level, up to highest you can cast.">
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpSourceEq"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioCloDrBlu" name="Cloak of the Dragon (Blue)" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 6,000 gp (10th) \n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Shoulders \n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 10th \n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 20); transmutation \n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151; and standard \n{b}Weight{/b}: 1 lb.\n\n{i}This cloak consists of layers of tiny scales affixed to a thin leather backing.{/i}\n\nTen varieties of this item exist, each corresponding in hue to one of the five chromatic or the five metallic dragons. While you wear the cloak, you gain a +1 enhancement bonus to your natural armor bonus.\n\nIf you worship Bahamut or Tiamat (or any other draconic deity), you may activate the {i}cloak of the dragon{/i} once per day to grow a pair of draconic wings that grants you a fly speed (equal to your land speed) for 10 minutes. While this effect is active, you may use a breath weapon (as if you were a half-dragon matching the hue of your cloak; see MM 146) once. \n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 3,000 gp, 240 XP, 6 days. \n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}polymorph{/i}, worshiper of a draconic deity.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
