hero.childfound[xHlDBreath].field[CustDesc].text = "You have the ability to use a breath weapon once while the cloak of the dragon is activated as a Half Dragon of the same color as your cloak."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioCloDrCop" name="Cloak of the Dragon (Copper)" description="{b}Price (Item Level){/b}: 6,000 gp (10th) \n{b}Body Slot{/b}: Shoulders \n{b}Caster Level{/b}: 10th \n{b}Aura{/b}: Moderate (DC 20); transmutation \n{b}Activation{/b}: &#151; and standard \n{b}Weight{/b}: 1 lb.\n\n{i}This cloak consists of layers of tiny scales affixed to a thin leather backing.{/i}\n\nTen varieties of this item exist, each corresponding in hue to one of the five chromatic or the five metallic dragons. While you wear the cloak, you gain a +1 enhancement bonus to your natural armor bonus.\n\nIf you worship Bahamut or Tiamat (or any other draconic deity), you may activate the {i}cloak of the dragon{/i} once per day to grow a pair of draconic wings that grants you a fly speed (equal to your land speed) for 10 minutes. While this effect is active, you may use a breath weapon (as if you were a half-dragon matching the hue of your cloak; see MM 146) once. \n\n{i}Cost to Create{/i}: 3,000 gp, 240 XP, 6 days. \n\n{i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}polymorph{/i}, worshiper of a draconic deity.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Wondrous">
