  <thing id="gPwCAngBlo" name="Angel Blood" description="Those who manage to shed celestial blood often collect a few drops for sale to other, equally vile souls. When blended with specific poisons and used as a component in the casting of any spell that has the evil descriptor, angel&apos;s blood increases the save DC by 1. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 85 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="85"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCAshPwr" name="Ashes of Power" description="When a used scroll is burned and its ashes are mixed with holy water and mystical inks, the resulting paste houses an ember of true magic. When used as a component in the casting of {i}dispel magic{/i}, {i}greater dispel magic{/i}, or {i}break enchantment{/i}, this powder allows the caster to make two dispel checks and choose the better result. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 1,750 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="1750"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCAurSap" name="Aurial Sapphire" description="On rare occasions, the winds of the Elemental Plane of Air capture various particles whipping about in the emptiness and drive them together over the course of years. The result is a crystal marbled in various shades of blue. Called aurial sapphires, these gemstones are sometimes found on the Material Plane, usually at high altitudes where the winds blow most fiercely. When an aurial sapphire is used as a component in the casting of any Air domain spell or spell that has the air descriptor, the spell is affected as if by the Quicken Spell feat, but without any level increase. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 215 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="215"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCCryPow" name="Crypt Powder" description="During the long years in which a powerful necromancer lies decaying in his tomb, some of the magic that infused his bones seeps into the surrounding walls. If one of these stones is then shattered in a particular way, the resulting dust sometimes retains that power. When used as a component in the casting of any spell that targets either corpses or undead, this powder increases both the save DC and the caster level by 1. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 180 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="150"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCDopBil" name="Doppleganger Bile" description="This viscous fluid aids in deceptive magic. When specially distilled and used as a component in the casting of any spell that grants invisibility or a bonus on Disguise checks, doppelganger bile doubles the duration of the effect. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 95 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="95"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCDrRuby" name="Dragon Ruby" description="Gold dragons like to feast on pearls and gems. Occasionally, a few gems pass through such a dragon&apos;s system undigested. If one of those gems is a ruby, it absorbs a bit of the creature&apos;s fiery nature and becomes a dragon ruby. When used as a component in the casting of any spell that has the fire descriptor, a dragon ruby doubles that spell&apos;s area. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 175 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="175"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCEssOrd" name="Essence of Order" description="When various powdered herbs are mixed with the inner fluids of an inevitable, the resulting oily substance emits a potent vapor known as essence of order. Anyone breathing this vapor is cured of 1 point of mental ability damage caused by a poison or disease. A single dose is usable only once. When used as a component in the casting of any spell that has the law descriptor, essence of order increases the save DC by 1. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 300 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="300"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCFeFaRe" name="Feather of the Far Reaches" description="When coated in a thin layer of powdered mithral, the tailfeathers of an albatross or an arrowhawk gain a degree of magical power. If one of these so-called feathers of the far reaches is used as a component in the casting of any Travel domain spell, it either adds 10 feet to the speed (if the spell grants a new or improved mode of movement) or increases the effective caster level by 1. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 95 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="95"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCGamFat" name="Game of Fate" description="Long ago, someone discovered that a die carved from the shell of a large tortoise attracts the attention of the deities of luck. When used as a component in the casting of any spell that grants a bonus on attack rolls, damage rolls, saving throws, or checks, such a die-known as a game of fate-produces one of three effects: +1 caster level (01-45), double duration (46-90), or restoration of a spell as per a {i}pearl of power{/i} (91-100). \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 550 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="550"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCGuaFea" name="Guardinal Feather" description="The feathers of a guardinal, when given freely, have protective properties. When one is used as a component in the casting of any spell that grants either energy resistance or a bonus to Armor Class, it increases the value of that protection by 2. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 600 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="600"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCHeroTe" name="Hero&apos;s Tears" description="Tears taken from a champion of good who weeps over a fallen comrade become a potent aid to virtuous casters when sanctified with {i}bless water{/i}. If these hero&apos;s tears are used as a component in the casting of any spell that has the good descriptor, they increase the effective caster level by 2. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 675 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="675"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCHornGo" name="Horn of Gorgon" description="Gorgon horns soften when soaked in a particular kind of rare vinegar. If this horn of gorgon is then used as a component in the casting of any spell that enhances Strength-whether by an enhancement bonus, a size increase, or any other means-it adds 2 to the subject&apos;s Strength, on top of the spell&apos;s normal effects. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 575 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="575"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCKisDis" name="Kiss of Discord" description="An herb known by sages as lusiri blossom, kiss of discord has dull red leaves that vaguely resemble lips. When ingested, it causes hallucinations (ld3 hours, Fort DC 13 negates, treat as {i}confusion{/i}). If used as a component in the casting of any spell that has the chaos descriptor, it increases the effective caster level by 2. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 310 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="310"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCObaLea" name="Obaddis Leaf" description="A rare variety of holly, this plant retains some of the magic that passes through it when it is used as a divine focus by a druid. If it is then used as a component in the casting of a Plant domain spell or any spell that specifically targets plants, it doubles both the area and the duration. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 130 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="130"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCPeaWav" name="Pearl of the Waves" description="A pearl of the waves results when an oyster forms a pearl around the tiniest fragment of a magic item, such as a sliver of a magic blade or wood from a broken staff. If this pearl is used as a component in the casting of any Water domain spell or a spell that has the water descriptor, the spell is affected as if by the Quicken Spell feat, but without any change in spell slot. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 225 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="225"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCSchDre" name="Scholar&apos;s Dreams" description="Some say that ivy growing on the gravestone of a truly learned sage feeds upon the knowledge of the deceased. When used as a component in the casting of any Knowledge domain spell, this ivy-known as scholar&apos;s dreams-doubles both the range and the duration. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 175 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="175"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCSoiSto" name="Soil of Stone" description="Taken from beneath the palaces of the dao (genie&apos;s of Elemental Earth), this powdered stone retains traces of both that plane and its masters. If this so-called soil of stone is used as a component in the casting of any Earth domain spell or a spell that has the earth descriptor, it doubles the duration. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 65 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="65"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCSunPel" name="Sunflower of Pelor" description="For reasons unfathomable to sages, large sunflowers often grow in the soil where an undead creature has been reduced to ash by a cleric&apos;s turn undead ability. The petals of these sunflowers of Pelor, if properly treated with various unguents, grant power to sun-related spells. When used as a component in the casting of any Sun domain spell or a spell that has the light descriptor, these petals double its area. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 100 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="100"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCTalEhl" name="Talon of Ehlonna" description="When an animal dies while under the effect of a {i}magic fang{/i} or {i}greater magic fang{/i} spell, one of its claws or teeth sometimes retains a spark of that magic. This so-called talon of Ehlonna resists decay and gains a gold-bronze luster over time. When used as a component in the casting of any Animal domain spell or a spell that specifically targets animals, the talon increases the effective caster level by 2. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 370 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="370"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCTrWaBl" name="True Warrior&apos;s Blade" description="A weapon wielded by a deity&apos;s champion, then broken in combat, can be consecrated with holy water and unguents to become a true warrior&apos;s blade. When used as a component in the casting of any divine spell that deals hit point damage, this blade I increases the damage dealt by 2 points per spell level. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 650 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="650"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCTwiGre" name="Twilight Green" description="A distant relative of belladonna, this herb is a deadly poison (ingestion, DC 14 Fortitude negates, primary and secondary damage ld4 Constitution). When used as a component in the casting of any spell that deals negative energy damage, however, twilight green increases that damage by 1 point per spell level. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 250 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="250"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gPwCUniHor" name="Unicorn Horn" description="If a horn taken from a unicorn that has died of natural causes is used as a component in the casting of any touch spell that has the healing descriptor, it transforms the spell into a ray with a 30-foot range. \n\n{i}Price{/i}: 190 gp.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="190"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="PComponent" name="Power Component"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gHSErythul" name="Blood-Face of Erynthul" description="This rust-colored talisman depicts a face cackling with evil laughter. Swaths of blood-red highlight the open, grinning mouth and the brow ridge, giving the face a wild, almost demonic look. \n\nWhen used as a focus for illusion spells or spells with the chaotic designator, a blood-face of Erythnul increases the save DC by 1.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="350"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="HolySymbol" name="Holy Symbol"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gHSHextor" name="Barb of Hextor" description="The shape of this dark-colored, metallic talisman is that of a mailed fist grasping barbed arrows. \n\nWhen used to cast Evil domain spells or spells that have the evil descriptor, this symbol increases your effective caster level by 1.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="350"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="HolySymbol" name="Holy Symbol"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gHSHeiron" name="Bolt of Heironeous" description="Cast in the shape of a hand grasping a lightning bolt, this holy symbol is usually made of silver, gold, or a combination of both. \n\nWhen used to cast Good domain spells or spells that have the good descriptor, this symbol increases your effective caster level by 1.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="350"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="HolySymbol" name="Holy Symbol"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gHSNerull" name="Devastation of Nerull" description="This symbol is either carved from bone or made from the skeleton of a Diminutive creature, and it always appears to be decaying. Worshipers of Nerull typically either grow lichen on it, or whet it with a small amount of acid. As a result, it usually carries a mildly unpleasant odor. \n\nWhen used to cast a spell from the necromancy school or the Death domain, or when brandished to rebuke or command (not turn or destroy) unintelligent undead, this symbol increases your effective caster level by 1.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="350"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="HolySymbol" name="Holy Symbol"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gHSEhlonna" name="Ehlonna&apos;s Brooch" description="Worn by worshipers of the goddess of the woodlands, this emerald carving of a unicorn rampant sometimes seems to blend into the wearer&apos;s garb. When grasped and used as a focus for a spell, it exudes a faint green glow. \n\nWhen Ehlonna&apos;s brooch is used as a focus for a {i}summon nature&apos;s ally{/i} or {i}summon monster{/i} spell, each creature summoned gains +1 hit point per Hit Die.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Gear">
    <comment>Page 134 &#150; Ehlonna&#146;s Brooch
