  <thing id="sClrRavDar" name="Ravenous Darkness" description="{i}Tendrils of shadow leap from the object you&apos;ve touched, then swiftly form into an all-encompassing wave. The spreading night seems to blot out both light and life.{/i} \n\nThe object touched sheds darkness as a {i}deeper darkness{/i} spell (PH 217). In addition, every living creature within the area of the resulting darkness (a 60-foot radius) takes 1d6 points of negative energy damage per round. Any creature under the influence of an on going negative energy effect (such as negative levels or necromantic-based ability damage) instead takes 2d6 points of damage per round. This effect ends for a given creature if it moves out of the area of darkness but resumes should it reenter. A successful Fortitude save negates the damage, but the affected creature must repeat the save every round, whether it succeeds or fails. If a creature has spell resistance, the spell must overcome it to deal damage. \n\nAny undead creature within the darkness instead gains fast healing 1. \n\n{i}Ravenous darkness{/i} counters and dispels any light spell of equal or lower level." compset="Spell" summary="Touched object sheds darkness; living creatures nearby take 1d6/round negative energy damage while undead gain fast healing 1.">
