  <thing id="sClrSubAur" name="Subdue Aura" description="{i}The normally formidable aura that marks you as a servant of a higher power recedes, leaving few traces of your allegiance visible to creatures that can see such marks.{/i} \n\nThis spell masks the target&apos;s aura, making it appear less powerful than it really is. For every two caster levels, the target of a {i}subdue aura{/i} spell appears to have 1 fewer Hit Die than it really does. \n\nIf the target has no aura, the spell has no effect" compset="Spell" summary="Subject&#146;s aura weakens as if it had 1 HD/two caster levels fewer than it actually does.">
