  <thing id="sClrFooDiv" name="Footsteps of the Divine" description="{i}Your body twists and reshapes itself, allowing you brief freedom from the confines of a wholly humanoid shape. {/i}\n\nUpon casting this spell, you briefly acquire a new movement mode and speed, as given on the table below. Unlike most deity-variable spells, {i}footsteps of the divine{/i} does not limit you to the option offered by your own deity; you are free to choose any option presented on the table. If you choose an option offered by a deity other than your own, however, the spell duration is halved. You can choose only one option per casting. \n\nDeity&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Movement Mode&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Speed \nBahamut&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Fly&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;60 ft. (poor) \nBoccob&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Fly&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;40 ft. (perfect) \nCorellon Larethian&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;x&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;+40 ft. \nEhlonna&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Climb&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;30 ft. \nErythnul&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;x&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;+40 ft. \nFharlanghn&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;x&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;+50 ft. \nGarl Glittergold&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Burrow&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;20 ft. \nGruumsh&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Burrow&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;20 ft. \nHeironeous&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;x&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;+40 ft. \nHextor&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;x&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;+40 ft. \nKord&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Climb&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;30 ft. \nKurtulmak&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Burrow&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;20 ft. \nLolth&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Climb&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;30 ft. \nMoradin&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Burrow&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;20 ft. \nNerull&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Fly&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;50 ft. (average) \nObad-Hai&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;x&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;+40 ft. \nOlidammara&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Climb&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;30 ft. \nPelor&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Fly&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;50 ft. (average) \nSt. Cuthbert&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;x&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;+40 ft. \nTiamat&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Fly&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;60 ft. (poor) \nVecna&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Fly&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;40 ft. (perfect) \nWee Jas&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Burrow&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;20 ft. \nYondalla&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;Climb&#150;&#150;&#150;&#150;30 ft. \n\nYour assumption of a new movement mode, if any, imposes certain physical changes on you. For instance, if {i}footsteps of the divine{/i} grants you flight, you grow wings; if it grants you a burrow speed, you grow heavy digging claws; and so forth. A &quot;x&quot; entry indicates that you gain no new movement type, but your base speed increases by the amount indicated. \n\nAt any point before the duration expires, you can choose to employ a burst of truly inhuman speed. You can discharge the spell to add +10 feet to your speed per remaining round of the spell&#146;s duration. This effect lasts until the end of your turn." compset="Spell" summary="Gain a new movement type and speed based on the deity chosen.">
