  <thing id="sClrIntBle" name="Interfaith Blessing" description="{i}You feel your deity speaking through you to other gods, filling the space around you with diverse divine energies that strengthen your ally. {/i}\n\nWhen you cast {i}interfaith blessing{/i}, every creature within range is individually blessed by its own deity for the duration of the spell. The specific blessing gained depends on the particular deity worshiped, as given on the table below. A subject that venerates more than one deity must roll randomly to determine which blessing is received. The bonuses provided by this spell are sacred (if your deity is good or neutral) or profane (if your deity is evil).\n\n{b}Deity Blessing{/b} \nBahamut, St. Cuthbert, &#150;&#150;&#150;&#150; +1 on attack rolls and saves \nor Yondalla \n\nBoccob, Corellon &#150;&#150;&#150;&#150; +1 on attack rolls and skill checks \nLarethian, Vecna, or Wee Jas \n\nEhlonna, Obad-Hai, &#150;&#150;&#150;&#150; +1 on attack rolls and to AC \nor the general worship of nature \n\nErythnul, Gruumsh, or Lolth &#150;&#150;&#150;&#150; +2 on damage rolls \n\nFharlanghn, Moradin, or Pelor &#150;&#150;&#150;&#150; +2 to AC \n\nGarl Glittergold, &#150;&#150;&#150;&#150; Roll 1d8 to determine blessing; a result of 6 is player&apos;s choice \nOlidammara, or no deity \n\nHeironeous, Hextor, or Nerull &#150;&#150;&#150;&#150; +2 on attack rolls \n\nKord, Kurtulmak, &#150;&#150;&#150;&#150; +1 on attack rolls and damage rolls \nor Tiamat" compset="Spell" summary="Subjects gain combat benefits based on their individual deities.">
