  <thing id="fSpiritCo" name="Spiritual Counter" description="Your devotion and faith allow you to counter the effects of other spells.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Any other divine feat, ability to turn or rebuke undead.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard (readied) action, you can expend one or more turn or rebuke undead attempts to counter another caster&apos;s spell, as though you had cast the same spell yourself (see Counterspells, PH 170). You must spend a number of daily uses equal to 2 + the level of the spell you wish to counter (minimum 1) and be able to cast that spell as if it were on your spell list.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: You can counter a spell only by casting the same spell, a specific counterspell, or {i}dispel magic{/i}.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="Feat" summary="Standard, burn 2+spl level turn/rebuke to counter target spell as if cast same." uniqueness="useronce">
