  <thing id="xSunDevote" name="Sun Devotion" description="Your weapon blazes with the power of the sun.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Once per day as a swift action, you can cause one of your melee weapons to glow with the power of the sun. The illumination radius is the same as that of a torch, but the light is true sunlight and affects creatures within a 10-foot radius as such. This effect lasts for 1 minute.\n\nWhile your weapon glows, it deals an additional 1 point of sacred (if your deity is good or neutral) or profane (if your deity is evil) damage per character level you possess to any undead it strikes.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You can select this feat multiple times, gaining one additional daily use each time you take it.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: If you have the ability to turn or rebuke undead, you gain one additional daily use of this feat for each daily turn or rebuke use you expend." compset="Special" summary="X/day, swift, melee weap glows 1 min w/ 10 ft true sunlight, +Y dam to undead." uniqueness="unique">
