  <thing id="cMythExemp" name="Mythic Exemplar" description="&quot;{i}Nobody today can match the great heroes of the epic past. But by following closely in their footsteps, perhaps we can come close!{/i}&apos;\n&#151;Mikolai Laziros, mythic exemplar\n\n{b}Special{/b}: Must be a member of the Disciples of Legend.\n\nFew are as devoted to history as the Disciples of Legend, and none among that august group are as committed to their paragons as the mythic exemplars. True followers&#151;even worshipers&#151;of the Six from Shadow (see Complete Champion pg 65), the mythic exemplars model their skills, their attitudes, and even their lives after those fabled heroes.\n\n{b}BECOMING A MYTHIC EXEMPLAR{/b}\nBecause the mythic exemplar prestige class offers a number of &quot;paths, &quot; each modeled on one of the Six from Shadow, it is open to a wide variety of entrants. It is best suited to clerics, fighters, marshals, rangers, rogues, and wizards.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="ClassLevel" maxlimit="10">
    <fieldval field="cHitDice" value="8"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="ClassType" tag="Prestige"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cHelpMEx"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="helper" thing="cHelpMEx"/>
    <exprreq message="Knowledge (history) 3 ranks required"><![CDATA[#skillranks[kKnowHist] >= 3]]></exprreq>
    <prereq message="One of the following: base attack bonus +5, able to cast 3rd-level spells, sneak attack +2d6, or ability to grant allies a bonus on attack rolls, saves, or checks as an extraordinary ability.">
      <validate><![CDATA[ 
@valid = 0
   var total as number
     total = 0
   if (child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 5) then
     total +=1
   endif
   if (tagcount[Hero.Arcane] >= 3 + 1) then
     total +=1
   endif
   if (childfound[xSneakAtt].field[Value].value >= 2) then
     total +=1
   endif         
     if (total >=1) then
       @valid = 1
     endif]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    <prereq message="One of the following: Diplomacy 7 ranks, Intimidate 7 ranks, Knowledge (arcana) 7 ranks, Knowledge (religion) 7 ranks, or Move Silently 7 ranks required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[
    @valid = 0
  if (#skillranks[kDiplomacy] >= 7) then
    @valid = 1
  elseif (#skillranks[kIntim] >= 7) then
    @valid = 1
  elseif (#skillranks[kKnowArcan] >= 7) then
    @valid = 1
  elseif (#skillranks[kKnowRel] >= 7) then
    @valid = 1
  elseif (#skillranks[kMoveSil] >= 7) then
    @valid = 1
  endif]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMExDaPath" name="Dardallion&apos;s Path" description="Upon becoming a mythic exemplar, you must choose one of the legendary Six from Shadow upon whom to model your skills and abilities. Your choices are the clever Dardallion, the faithful Imdastri, the all-knowing Ktolemagne, the inexorable Orsos, the noble and inspirational Sir Reikhardt, and the mighty Sunyartra. Once made, your choice cannot be changed." compset="CustomSpec" summary="Followers of Dardallion have good Reflex saves and focus on stealth." uniqueness="unique">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMEx"/>
    <eval phase="UserPreLv"><![CDATA[~ Get our level
      var level as number
      level = hero.child[cHelpMEx].field[cTotalLev].value

~ Set our name
      var total as number
      if (level >= 7) then
        total = 4
     elseif (level >= 5) then
        total = 3
      elseif (level >= 3) then
        total = 2
      elseif (level >= 1) then
        total = 1
        endif

~ Set our name
     hero.child[vRef].field[vBase].value += total]]></eval>
    <prereq message="Paragon already chosen.">
      <validate>@valid = 0
   if (picklives[cMExImPath] + picklives[cMExKtPath] + picklives[cMExOrPath] + picklives[cMExRePath] + picklives[cMExSuPath] = 0) then
     @valid = 1
   elseif (picklives[cMExDaPath] = 1) then
     @valid = 1
       endif</validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMExParaPa" name="Paragon&apos;s Path" description="Upon becoming a mythic exemplar, you must choose one of the legendary Six from Shadow upon whom to model your skills and abilities. Your choices are the clever Dardallion, the faithful Imdastri, the all-knowing Ktolemagne, the inexorable Orsos, the noble and inspirational Sir Reikhardt, and the mighty Sunyartra. Once made, your choice cannot be changed." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Choose one of the Six from Shadow to emulate.">
