    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMExEmbPar" name="Embody Paragon" description="When you reach 10th level, you truly embody every physical and spiritual concept that your paragon stood for. Unless otherwise noted, the ability you gain is permanent and constant, as long as you remain conscious. If it is suppressed, you can raise the effect again as a swift action.\n\n{i}Dardallion{/i}: You can turn incorporeal (DMG 294) for up 1 minute per day. This duration need not be used all at once and can be divided into intervals as short as 1 round. Shifting to or from incorporeality requires a move action.\n\n{i}Imdastri{/i}: You can &quot;lose&quot; a prepared divine spell in exchange for a spell of lower level from the Luck, Protection, or Strength domains, much as a good cleric can spontaneously cast cure spells. You do not gain the domain power or the ability to prepare these spells as domain spells.\n\n{i}Ktolemagne{/i}: You can &quot;lose&quot; a prepared arcane spell in exchange for any divination spell of lower level that is already in your spellbook.\n\n{i}Orsos: You gain a +4 bonus on any saves or rolls made resist fatigue and exhaustion. In addition, you are under permanent freedom of movement{/i} effect, unless the spell level of the impeding effect exceeds your character level.\n\n{i}Reikhardt{/i}: Select either Fortitude or Will saves. From this point on, you (and all allies within 60 feet) gain a circumstance bonus equal to your Charisma modifier on this saving throw. Once made, this choice cannot be changed.\n\nIn addition, for 10 rounds per day, you can grant yourself and each ally within 60 feet damage reduction 2/&#151;. This benefit does not stack with any other damage reduction you or your allies possess. This ability requires a swift action to activate.\n\n{i}Sunyartra{/i}: You can ignore 15 points of damage reduction (except epic) when attacking foes, and 15 points of hardness when striking inanimate objects." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Gain ultimate supernatural ability 1/day, based on chosen Paragon.">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="10"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMEx"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMExImPath" name="Imdastri&apos;s Path" description="Upon becoming a mythic exemplar, you must choose one of the legendary Six from Shadow upon whom to model your skills and abilities. Your choices are the clever Dardallion, the faithful Imdastri, the all-knowing Ktolemagne, the inexorable Orsos, the noble and inspirational Sir Reikhardt, and the mighty Sunyartra. Once made, your choice cannot be changed." compset="CustomSpec" summary="Followers of Imdastri have good Will saves and focus on faith." uniqueness="unique">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMEx"/>
    <eval phase="UserPreLv"><![CDATA[~ Get our level
      var level as number
      level = hero.child[cHelpMEx].field[cTotalLev].value

~ Set our name
      var total as number
      if (level >= 7) then
        total = 4
     elseif (level >= 5) then
        total = 3
      elseif (level >= 3) then
        total = 2
      elseif (level >= 1) then
        total = 1
        endif

~ Set our name
     hero.child[vWill].field[vBase].value += total]]></eval>
    <prereq message="Paragon already chosen.">
