  <thing id="cParaInit" name="Paragnostic Initiate" description="&quot;{i}Magic is only one kind of knowledge.{/i}&quot;\n&#151;Auleric the Swift, Paragnostic initiate\n\n{b}Special{/b}: Must be a member of the Paragnostic Assembly.\n\nNot all who follow the precepts of the Paragnostic Assembly (see Complete Champion 72) are spellcasters. Melee fighters, archers, and practitioners of mundane skills can also join the eternal hunt for knowledge. Paragnostic initiates, as the most devoted of these seekers are known, are no less dedicated to the hunt for secrets than are the apostles. Initiates, however, tend to focus less on magic and more on other aspects of the world. By combining their knowledge with their other abilities, they learn new ways to apply their skills and can even augment the beneficial magics that others cast upon them.\n\n{b}BECOMING A PARAGNOSTIC INITIATE{/b}\nRogues, scouts, and swashbucklers are the most common candidates for the Paragnostic initiate prestige class because of their mobility and access to skills. Fighters and rangers are far from uncommon, however.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="ClassLevel" maxlimit="3">
