  <thing id="cShadowspy" name="Shadowspy" description="&quot;{i}Perhaps you see it as a curse that I must deny myself the light of the Shining One so that his enemies might be exposed and destroyed. But it is my honor and duty to make such a sacrifice, and in truth, I see the gifts of the Shining One as proof that I am still within his sight, despite the shadows that cling to me.{/i}&quot;\n&#151;Saera, Shadow Knight of Pelor\n\nShadowspies are the covert arm of Pelor&apos;s Shadow Guard (see Complete Champion pg 75). Members of this subsect work individually or in small groups to locate hidden sources of evil. Although they often lead double lives, masquerading as normal folk who are simply trying to get by, shadowspies never forget their duty to their deity, to their church, and to the multitude of innocents who unknowingly depend on them.\n\n{b}BECOMING A SHADOWSPY{/b}\nOnly priests and paladins of Pelor with the proper skills and demeanor are permitted to join the shadowspies. The vast majority of shadowspies are drawn from the shadowstrikers (pg 108), though it is not unheard of for ordinary priests of Pelor to be inducted as shadowspies. Clerics or paladins with levels in bard, monk, ranger, or rogue are ideal candidates because they have the stealthy skills to use the shadows as a tool against the forces of darkness.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="ClassLevel" maxlimit="10">
    <fieldval field="cHitDice" value="6"/>
    <usesource source="CompChamp" parent="p35" name="Complete Champion"/>
    <tag group="AlgnReq" tag="Good"/>
    <tag group="ClassType" tag="Prestige"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cHelpSHP"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="helper" thing="cHelpSHP"/>
    <exprreq message="Gather Information 6 ranks required." onlyonce="yes"><![CDATA[#skillranks[kGatherInf] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Hide 6 ranks required." onlyonce="yes"><![CDATA[#skillranks[kHide] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Move Silently 6 ranks required." onlyonce="yes"><![CDATA[#skillranks[kMoveSil] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <prereq message="Good Devotion, Healing Devotion, Strength Devotion, or Sun Devotion required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[var x as number

x = (#hasfeat[fGoodDev] + #hasfeat[fHealDev] + #hasfeat[fStrDev] + #hasfeat[fSunDev]) 

if (x >= 1) then
  @valid = 1
  endif]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    <prereq message="Must be a cleric or paladin.">
      <validate><![CDATA[var x as number

x = (#levelcount[Cleric] + #levelcount[Paladin]) 

if (x >= 1) then
  @valid = 1
  endif]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    <prereq message="Ability to cast 1st-level Divine spells required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[validif (tagcount[Hero.Divine] >= 1 + 1)]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
