  <thing id="cvBrdHealH" name="Healing Hymn" description="When you play your healing hymn, your allies can cast curative spells more effectively. Furthermore, everyone around you feels rejuvenated and more fully rested when your hymn becomes a lullaby.\n\n{b}Replaces{/b}: This benefit replaces the {i}fascinate{/i} bardic music ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: If you have 3 or more ranks in a Perform skill, you can use your music or poetics to create an area conducive to healing.\n\nTo be affected, an ally must be able to see and hear you perform. The effect lasts as long as you continue performing and for 5 rounds thereafter. An affected ally who casts any conjuration (healing) spell gains a +1 sacred (if you&apos;re good or neutral) or profane (if you&apos;re evil) bonus on the roll for each rank you have in the Perform skill. The bonus is limited by the maximum caster level bonus of a curing spell. For example, if a level 10 cleric cast cure serious while under the effect of healing hymn used by a bard with 10 ranks in perform, the cure serious spell would only cure 3d8+15 instead of 3d8+20. This ability has no effect on spells cast from wands, scrolls, or other magic items.\n\nIn addition, if you use this ability for at least 1 minute before you and your allies retire for the night, everyone in the group heals naturally at the end of the rest as if he had completed 24 hours of best rest (thus recovering twice his character level in hit points). If the music is interrupted, the magic of the song is lost.\n\nEither use of {i}healing hymn{/i} counts as one daily use of your bardic music ability. Healing hymn lasts as long as you concentrate up to a maximum of 2 minutes. This is a spell-like ability.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
