  <thing id="cvHymnFort" name="Hymn of Fortification" description="By singing praises to the holy powers, you can cloak yourself or an ally in a protective sheath of sound. This effect protects the subject from supernatural creatures, as well as their malign powers.\n\n{b}Replaces{/b}: This benefit replaces the inspire competence bardic music ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: If you are a 3rd-level or higher bard with 6 or more ranks in Perform (oratory) or Perform (sing), you can grant protection from supernatural creatures. This effect fortifies you or a single chosen ally within 30 feet against mental control and attacks from evil-aligned or summoned creatures. In most respects, {i}hymn of fortification{/i} mirrors the effects of the {i}protection from evil{/i} spell. If you wish to protect an ally with this ability, the two of you must be able to see and hear each other. The effect lasts as long as you concentrate, up to a maximum of 2 minutes.\n\nEach use of {i}hymn of fortification{/i} counts as one daily use of your bardic music ability. This is a spell-like ability.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
