  <thing id="cvUndKnigh" name="Underdark Knight" description="If you dedicate yourself to overcoming evil in the Underdark, you might find little use for the paladin&apos;s most prized ally, the special mount. By giving up the ability to call this devoted creature, you become a more mobile and effective fighter underground.\n\n{b}Replaces{/b}: This benefit replaces the {i}special mount{/i} class feature.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Whenever you are underground, you can draw upon the earth to gain the following abilities.\n\nAt 5th level, your base speed increases by 10 feet, and you gain a +2 circumstance bonus on Balance, Climb, and Jump checks. You also gain low-light vision that functions as long as you remain underground. If you already had low-light vision, you instead gain darkvision out to 60 feet while underground; if you already had darkvision, add 30 feet to its range.\n\nAt 7th level, you can use {i}spike stones{/i} once per day, as the spell (this is a spell-like ability with caster level equal to your character level).\n\nAt 12th level, you gain the earth glide extraordinary ability, which enables you to move through stone, dirt, or almost any other sort of earth except metal as easily as a fish moves through water (MM 98). If you end your movement inside earth or stone, however, you begin to suffocate (DMG 304).\n\nAt 15th level, you can use {i}dimension door{/i}, as the spell, once per day for every five paladin levels you possess (this is a spell-like ability with caster level equal to your character level). You must begin and end any such movement in contact with stone or earth." compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
