  <thing id="cvSpiGuide" name="Spiritual Guide" description="You are befriended by a spiritual guide that speaks to you and aids you as long as you remain in the wilderness.\n\n{b}Replaces{/b}: This benefit replaces the animal companion class feature.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You gain a spiritual guide. As long as you remain in natural surroundings (including underground caverns), this guide is a constant companion. Once you enter any civilized area larger than a hamlet, however, your spiritual guide leaves your side, returning only when you return to the wilds.\n\nAlthough it cannot protect you from harm, your spiritual guide can warn you of impending danger. As long as your spiritual guide is with you, you gain a divine bonus equal to one-quarter your ranger level (rounded down) on Handle Animal, Knowledge (nature), Listen, Search, Spot, and Survival checks. In addition, you can use {i}commune with nature{/i}, as the spell, once per day as a full round action (with caster level equal to your character level). You can also prepare and cast this spell normally from your ranger spell list.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Champion" compset="ClassVary" uniqueness="unique">
